as you read, which helps you read faster. As you learn to read faster, you can increase the app&#39;s speed so the words appear on your screen faster. Boba and Rapid Reader also allow users to set their reading speed and adjust it as they improve.","<strong>Android Users</strong>: The top speed-reading apps available to Android users are ReadMe!, SpeedRead with Spritz and Reading Trainer.  SpeedRead with Spritz is similar to the ReadMe! app when it comes to how readers see the text. You set the speed incrementally and read the words as they appear in the text box. Once again, the goal here is to reduce your eye movement, so you just focus on the words in the box and read faster. As your reading skills improve, you can change the set speed.","Reading Trainer is a little different. This particular app features 12 exercises to help you increase your reading speed, including eye-movement tasks. By using this app, you can learn a few techniques that will improve your reading speed.","<strong>Speed Reading Software</strong><br/>While apps help increase your reading speed, if you are serious about speed reading, you want to purchase speed reading software. Most speed reading apps only use one technique to help you read faster. Alternatively, speed reading software presents you with several techniques and tricks to help you increase your reading speed while simultaneously comprehending the information.","It&#39;s pointless to speed read if you aren&#39;t able to retain comprehension of what you&#39;ve read. With more extensive training and exercises, you can speed-read at an advanced level and retain the information with no problem.","You can use speed reading for studying, recreational reading and more. Depending upon your commitment to and your interest in the skill, you can either use an app compatible with your phoneÂ s operating system or purchase software to help you reach your speed-reading goals."]},"id":"b424813e-9818-4a22-9476-54169f67a0a6","type":"text"}]],"body"